ğŸ§­ 1. WHAT ARE XPATH AXES?
Axes = directions to move inside HTML.
HTML is like a family tree:
â€¢	parent
â€¢	child
â€¢	sibling
â€¢	ancestor
â€¢	descendant
â€¢	following
â€¢	preceding
CSS cannot move UP. XPath can.
Thatâ€™s why axes are powerful.
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 2. CHILD AXIS
Means: "Select children of this element"
XPath:
//div[@class='product']/child::h2
Playwright:
await page.locator("//div[@class='product']/child::h2");
ğŸ‘‰ Returns the <h2> inside every product.
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 3. PARENT AXIS
Means: "Go upward"
//span[@class='price']/parent::div
Example: find the div product of a price.
Playwright:
await page.locator("//span[@class='price']/parent::div");
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 4. ANCESTOR AXIS
More powerful: Go up ANY levels
//span[text()='â‚¹80,000']/ancestor::div[@class='product']
Playwright:
await page.locator("//span[text()='â‚¹80,000']/ancestor::div[@class='product']");
ğŸŸ¢ Use this for finding the card when you only know a small text inside it.
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 5. DESCENDANT AXIS
Means: All children + grandchildren + deep elements
//div[@class='product']/descendant::button
Playwright:
await page.locator("//div[@class='product']/descendant::button");
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 6. SIBLING AXES (VERY IMPORTANT)
Siblings = same parent.
HTML example:
<h2>Samsung</h2>      â† sibling
<span>â‚¹80,000</span>  â† sibling
<p>desc</p>           â† sibling
<button>Buy</button>  â† sibling
________________________________________
6.1 following-sibling
Means: Select siblings that come AFTER this element
Example: get price after Samsung:
//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following-sibling::span
Playwright:
await page.locator("//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following-sibling::span");
________________________________________
6.2 preceding-sibling
Means: Select siblings that come BEFORE this element
Example: find h2 that comes before Buy button:
//button[@class='buy']/preceding-sibling::h2
Playwright:
await page.locator("//button[@class='buy']/preceding-sibling::h2");
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 7. FOLLOWING AXIS
Means: Everything after the element in the entire page flow.
(Not only siblings!)
Example: all elements after Samsung name:
//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following::*
Playwright:
await page.locator("//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following::*");
________________________________________
ğŸš€ 8. PRECEDING AXIS
Everything before the element in page flow:
//button[@class='buy']/preceding::*
Playwright:
await page.locator("//button[@class='buy']/preceding::*");
________________________________________
ğŸ”¥ Most Useful Real Automation Examples
________________________________________
âœ” 1. Click Buy button of Samsung (child â†’ parent â†’ descendant)
//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/ancestor::div[@class='product']//button
Playwright:
await page.locator("//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/ancestor::div[@class='product']//button").click();
________________________________________
âœ” 2. Get the price next to the name using sibling
//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following-sibling::span
Playwright:
await page.locator("//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following-sibling::span").textContent();
________________________________________
âœ” 3. Get product description using following-sibling
//h2[text()='Samsung S24']/following-sibling::p
________________________________________
âœ” 4. Get product title from Buy button (reverse direction)
//button[@class='buy']/preceding-sibling::h2
Playwright:
await page.locator("//button[@class='buy']/preceding-sibling::h2");
________________________________________
ğŸ’¡ SUPER SIMPLE SUMMARY
Axis	Meaning	Example
child	down	parent/child
parent	up	child/..
ancestor	up many levels	child/ancestor::div
descendant	down many levels	div/descendant::button
following-sibling	after same parent	h2/following-sibling::span
preceding-sibling	before same parent	button/preceding-sibling::h2
following	everything after	h2/following::span
preceding	everything before	button/preceding::*



